        <h2>Wordle Tips</h2>
        <ol class=3D"help">
            <li>Start with a strong <a href=3D"https://helpwordle.com/start=
-words">opening word</a> =E2=80=93 Choose a word with at least two or three=
 vowels and a mix of common consonants (e.g., CRANE, ADIEU).</li>
            <li>Avoid reusing eliminated letters&gt; =E2=80=93 If a letter =
has been ruled out, don=E2=80=99t include it in future guesses.</li>
            <li>Remember that letters can repeat =E2=80=93 Words may contai=
n double letters, such as SHEEP or LLAMA.</li>
            <li>More common words are more likely =E2=80=93 Wordle=E2=80=99=
s answer list favours familiar words over obscure ones.</li>
            <li>Plural words ending in 'S' aren't included =E2=80=93 For ex=
ample, DESKS won=E2=80=99t be an answer.</li>
            <li>Use strategic guesses to eliminate letters =E2=80=93 Instea=
d of trying to solve the word immediately, pick a word that helps narrow do=
wn possibilities.<br>
            <strong>Example:</strong>If you have _OOSE, the answer could be=
 GOOSE, LOOSE, MOOSE, NOOSE. A good word to guess would be GOLEM=E2=80=94it=
 won=E2=80=99t be the answer, but it tests multiple key letters.</li>
            <li>If 'E' is eliminated, consider words ending in =E2=80=98Y=
=E2=80=99 =E2=80=93 Many words that don=E2=80=99t contain E may end in Y (e=
.g., PARTY, FUNNY).</li>
            <li>Take your time =E2=80=93 There's no time limit, so think th=
rough each guess carefully</li>
